      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>Why open source matters for device management</h3>
          <p>Your device management platform sees everything on your endpoints. You should be able to see everything about it.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-cards">
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Inspect everything</p>
              <p>Security teams can audit exactly how devices are managed, how data flows, and what the agent does. No black boxes. Code you can read, test, and verify.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Every component public on GitHub</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">No vendor lock-in</p>
              <p>Your device configuration lives in Git, not a proprietary database. Run it as a <a href="/on-premise">self-hosted MDM</a> or let us host it. Either way, your data and configuration come with you.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>YAML in your repo, not our cloud</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Community driven</p>
              <p>Fleet's roadmap is shaped by the community, not just paying customers. Feature requests, bug reports, and code contributions move the product forward for everyone.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Public roadmap in GitHub Issues</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Extend and customize</p>
              <p>Build integrations, automate workflows, and customize Fleet without waiting for vendor approval. The API is comprehensive, and the code is yours to read and adapt.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Full REST API and source access</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Transparency for end users</p>
              <p>Employees can see exactly what's monitored on their work devices. Fleet Desktop links to the source code so people know what their company sees, and what it doesn't.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Built-in trust for the people you support</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Proven at scale</p>
              <p>Fleet runs in production at companies managing hundreds of thousands of endpoints across macOS, Windows, and <a href="/linux-management">Linux</a>. Open source doesn't mean hobbyist. It means software that earns trust through transparency.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Used by Stripe, Fastly, Gusto, and more</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


