      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>Self-hosted by design</h3>
          <p>Open-source MDM means you choose where it runs. Deploy Fleet on your own infrastructure, run it across every operating system, or let us host it.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-cards">
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Self-hosted MDM</p>
              <p>Run Fleet on AWS, GCP, Azure, bare metal, or in air-gapped networks. Every feature ships to self-hosted on the same day as cloud, no tier lock.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p><a href="/on-premise">On-premise deployment</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Open-source Linux MDM</p>
              <p>Manage Linux alongside macOS and Windows. Run scripts, enforce policies, monitor compliance, and track vulnerabilities across every distribution.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p><a href="/linux-management">Linux device management</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Open-source endpoint management</p>
              <p>Inventory, policies, software, vulnerability data, and MDM in one platform. Auditable code from the agent to the dashboard.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p><a href="/device-management">Explore device management</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
